    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of large evergreen spruce native to the western Himalaya and adjacent mountains, from Afghanistan to Nepal, 44 m in height and growing at altitudes of 3,600 m in forests together with deodar cedar, pindrow fir, and blue pine.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
